&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PHARMACY INVOICING CLERK&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;£21,789 to £23,121 pa Inclusive of HCAS (15%)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;37.5 HOURS PER WEEK (PART TIME HOURS WOULD BE CONSIDERED)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic Invoicing Clerk to join our friendly team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for processing invoices and necessary associated credit notes through the Pharmacy Computer System.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must have a minimum of 12-months experience working with stock control systems or invoicing experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent communication skills on both a verbal and written basis are required as you will be dealing with a wide range of people, both externally and within the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that if you are shortlisted for interview, these will be taking place on 26th November 2020 via MS Teams (non-transferable).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information, please contact Bernie Chapman, Pharmacy Purchasing Coordinator on 020 8934 2094.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameBernie ChapmanJob titlePurchasing CoordinatorEmail addressberniechapman@nhs.netTelephone number020 8934 2094&lt;/p&gt;
